        "assistant": "Based on your definition, **YON differs from Markdown in purpose, structure, and parsing model**.\n\n| Feature | YON | Markdown |\n|---|---|---|\n| Primary purpose | Constructed notation for **AI cognition** | Lightweight human-readable document formatting |\n| Main use | Structured, stream-first records for parsing/validation/action | Writing prose, docs, notes, README files, web content |\n| Parsing model | Each line is a **self-contained record** | Document-oriented; meaning often depends on surrounding lines |\n| Grammar | Fixed minimal grammar plus pluggable domain vocabularies | Informal/lightweight markup syntax with many dialects |\n| Output target | Machine/AI-readable cognition and action streams | Rendered human-readable documents, usually HTML |\n| Streaming behavior | Designed to be parsed and acted on as each line arrives | Not inherently stream-first |\n| Error behavior | A bad record can be isolated to one line | Formatting ambiguity or malformed structure may affect surrounding document |\n| Semantics | Domain vocabularies provide explicit meaning | Mostly presentation/formatting semantics |\n\nIn short:\n\n**Markdown is for formatting human-readable text.**  \nIt tells a renderer things like: this is a heading, this is a list, this is emphasized text, this is a code block.\n\n**YON is for structured AI-readable cognition/output.**  \nIt is designed so each line is a complete record that can be parsed, validated, or acted upon immediately.\n\nA key distinction is that Markdown is intentionally loose and prose-friendly. For example, the meaning of a line may depend on whether it is inside a list, blockquote, table, or fenced code block. That makes it convenient for humans, but less ideal as a strict action-oriented stream.\n\nYON, by contrast, is defined around:\n\n1. **minimal fixed grammar**,  \n2. **domain-specific vocabularies**, and  \n3. **stream-first self-contained records**.\n\nSo the short version is:\n\n> **Markdown structures documents for humans; YON structures cognition records for machines and AI systems.**",
